{"id":"1812.03162","submitter":"Baiying Liu","authors":"Dihua Jiang, Baiying Liu, and Bin Xu","title":"A reciprocal branching problem for automorphic representations and\n  global Vogan packets","comments":"Comments are welcome","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT math.RT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $G$ be a group and $H$ be a subgroup of $G$. The classical branching rule\n(or symmetry breaking) asks: For an irreducible representation $\\pi$ of $G$,\ndetermine the occurrence of an irreducible representation $\\sigma$ of $H$ in\nthe restriction of $\\pi$ to $H$. The reciprocal branching problem of this\nclassical branching problem is to ask: For an irreducible representation\n$\\sigma$ of $H$, find an irreducible representation $\\pi$ of $G$ such that\n$\\sigma$ occurs in the restriction of $\\pi$ to $H$. For automorphic\nrepresentations of classical groups, the branching problem has been addressed\nby the well-known global Gan-Gross-Prasad conjecture. In this paper, we\ninvestigate the reciprocal branching problem for automorphic representations of\nspecial orthogonal groups using the twisted automorphic descent method as\ndeveloped in [JZ15]. The method may be applied to other classical groups as\nwell.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Dec 2018 18:52:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-10"}
